  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You place a curse on willing creatures, forcing them to carry out some service or refrain from some action.</em></p><p><strong>Curse</strong></p><p>Your target(s) must be willing to be placed under a Geas. Each target is &amp;reference[cursed].</p><ul><li><p>You and the targets must agree on the contract before the spell is cast. The targets must understand the contract they agree to, or the spell fails. The contract usually includes a time or a condition that causes the Geas to end.</p></li><li><p>Once per day, if the target acts in a manner directly counter to the contract, they make a save.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Charisma Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 10d10 psychic]] damage* and suffers 2 levels of &amp;reference[exhaustion].</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage, and target suffers 1 level of exhaustion.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 2d10]] for each spell level above 5th level.</p><p></p><p><em>The target never takes damage if the believe they are following the original contract. If they are tricked into breaking the terms of the Geas, they must try to rectify their error if possible.</em></p><p><em>A @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.Mi4qWwfmDYv6GrkI]{Greater Restoration} or @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.5e0swEflzMmSszQ0]{Wish} spell can end the Geas.</em></p>",
      "chat": "<p><strong>Curse</strong></p><p>Your target(s) must be willing to be placed under a Geas. Each target is &amp;reference[cursed].</p><ul><li><p>You and the targets must agree on the contract before the spell is cast. The targets must understand the contract they agree to, or the spell fails. The contract usually includes a time or a condition that causes the Geas to end.</p></li><li><p>Once per day, if the target acts in a manner directly counter to the contract, they make a save.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Charisma Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 10d10 psychic]] damage* and suffers 2 levels of &amp;reference[exhaustion].</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage, and target suffers 1 level of exhaustion.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 2d10]] for each spell level above 5th level.</p><p></p><p><em>The target never takes damage if the believe they are following the original contract. If they are tricked into breaking the terms of the Geas, they must try to rectify their error if possible.</em></p><p><em>A @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.Mi4qWwfmDYv6GrkI]{Greater Restoration} or @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.5e0swEflzMmSszQ0]{Wish} spell can end the Geas.</em></p>"
    },
